    {
      "id": "33e19489-c708-42d5-bde5-98fab3f23b8c",
      "title": "IMPORTANT ISSUES IDENTIFIED",
      "subsections": [
        {
          "id": "353ba10c-7eeb-4488-8683-7aa549d693f8",
          "title": "TRACS Citations",
          "bullets": [
            {
              "id": "56283776-1fb1-48c0-8258-65c6fd3493ac",
              "content": "<p>Missing Citation Numbers in axon.citation Datastore view — FINDINGS</p>"
            },
            {
              "id": "ea5a4a7c-d2ea-4ad1-8710-063f0dd4f294",
              "content": "<p>The TRACS integration initially recognizes the citation number, then checks for an associated incident. If an incident exists, a custom field replaces the citation number with the incident number as the unique identifier.</p>"
            },
            {
              "id": "84f50770-458e-48b8-8843-b0667c737fad",
              "content": "<p>If no incident number is available, the custom field uses the event ID entered by the officer in the Agency Report Number field in TRACS.</p>"
            },
            {
              "id": "dd63b812-0ab0-45d5-82e2-24b0a8190c82",
              "content": "<p>Because the custom field overwrites the citation number with either the incident number or event ID, the citation number is not retained in the UI or the datastore.</p>"
            },
            {
              "id": "14cb8e31-9a8f-4cbd-b983-62a93f14708b",
              "content": "<p>If needed, the integration can be updated to preserve the citation number through the Integrations Scope Change process.</p>"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
